title: Not the Matrix
body:
Morning of February 24, 2019. Sunday.

        Dream #: 19,060-03. Reading time: 1 min 50 sec.

        This dream was one of those extraordinarily long meandering types with no discernible cohesion. It began as an end of the world theme where only a few people remain on Earth. However, there is significant ambiguity as there are also unrelated scenes with typical dreaming processes.

        There is a series of events that involves walking back and forth to one of two ends of a long colonnade in an unknown city. On one end is a laboratory where people are developing a vaccine to help people survive in the world as it presently is. Amanda Tapping is there, but I am unaware of her celebrity status. There is vague reasoning that I might be in a movie, but it does not take hold. They are trying to get the formula right and plan on using it on the people at the other end of the colonnade.

        I notice an abandoned car in one area of the colonnade, but it seems someone had worked on its engine recently. It is facing the street.

        At one point, I am supposed to be a messenger for Amanda’s group, but another group seems to want to stop the scientists. They approach the area, but I end up running around and phasing through their bodies as they walk to the other end of the colonnade to the group that is developing the vaccine.

        I fly above the Golden Gate bridge, looking straight down. I get a vague impression that I am dreaming, but it is not a full realization.

        In one of the last scenes where my dream becomes more ambiguous to its original implications, I see Keanu Reeves (around 30) come out of a small store in a business district. I recognize him and ask him which movie he enjoyed making the most. He answers with “The Matrix.” I start to chat with him about other concepts, but he soon seems annoyed and briskly walks away from me to cross the street.

        Even after tens of thousands of resolved dreams in over 50 years, it is rare to have more than one character linked to preconscious or interconsciousness processes, even more so in what appears to be reinduction personifications (which, as here, run away from me during the waking process). Keanu Reeves, in this case, had the dynamics of a reinduction process and the association with trying to subliminally stay in (and manipulate) a dream as an analogy to “The Matrix.” (This process is similar to many others, associated with events such as the wake-up scene in “The Matrix” and even my “The Dead One” dream from 1971). The association with injections comes from natural melatonin mediation, but of which is far more often only rendered as water in various forms each sleep cycle.
